Term::Shell::Pluggable

There is Term::Shell module in the first place. This is hybrid of that
one with Module::Pluggable. So you could add command line hooks to your
big and scary multi-module perl application.

http://search.cpan.org/~pin/Term-Shell-Pluggable/lib/Term/Shell/Pluggable.pm

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Term::Shell::Pluggable

You can also look for information at:

    http://github.com/pin/term-shell-pluggable

